    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>onion</strong>, <strong>carrot discs</strong>,<strong> bay leaf[ves]</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Tip: If your carrots are still a bit crunchy don't worry, these will be baked in the oven later!</p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
